 
<p>
Life in the ocean depths feeds on organic detritus that falls from
nearer the surface. 
<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/apr/27/life-in-oceans-twilight-zone-could-disappear-amid-warming-seas">With global heating, more of the detritus gets
eaten by microbes</a>
and never reaches the depths.  Almost half of the
deep ocean life could disappear in this century.

<p>
 